## Discovery Phase 14 — Key Findings

### Critical (6)
- P14-003: ChallengeType uses magic strings, not enum
- P14-004: ChallengeDifficulty uses magic strings, not enum
- P14-005: AlarmEvent.Type uses magic strings, not enum
- P14-018: No AlarmAppError enum spec (thiserror)
- P14-019: No IPC error response format defined
- P14-027: No Rust error enum spec despite thiserror in deps

### Medium (17)
- 9 magic string types needing enums (RepeatType TS, SoundCategory, SettingsValueType, ThemeMode, ExportFormat, ExportScope, DuplicateAction, ImportMode, SortField)
- 4 feature files missing acceptance criteria
- PascalCase violations in IPC payloads
- Settings seeding not specified
- No frontend state management spec
- No loading/empty/error UI states spec

### Low (6)
- Missing boolean semantic inverses
- Single-DB decision undocumented vs split-DB
- No config version tracking

